Author: thinking-throwaway
Text: I feel you. My coach tells me to workout my upper body and lift weights and that more muscles=more calories burned, which I like, but whenever I do weightlifting I can't help but feel like I'm wasting my time because cardio burns more calories in the moment. Also the fact that to workout you need to eat sufficient amounts of healthy food kills me because I just want to eat a tiny amount of junk food or restrict all the time.
